 "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Read the contents of the `input/qc/` directory to understand the structure and data within the `.cellsum` and `.libsum` files.\\n2. Process the `.libsum` files to create two wide tables: `scrna_qc.libstats_reads.tsv` and `scrna_qc.libstats_pct.tsv`.\\n3. Process the `.cellsum` files to normalize reads/UMI per cell by per-sample sum * 1e6.\\n4. Generate the required PNG plots:\\n   - `scrna_qc.reads_UMI_plot.png`\\n   - `scrna_qc.plate_cUPM.png`\\n   - `scrna_qc.plate_cRPM.png`\\n   - `scrna_qc.plate_abs_transcripts.png`\\n5. Save all outputs in the `output/` directory.\\n6. Verify the presence of `output/scrna_qc.reads_UMI_plot.png` and submit the task as complete.\\n\\n### Detailed Steps\\n\\n- **Step 2:**\\n  - Extract metrics from `.libsum` files and organize them into wide tables for reads and percentages.\\n\\n- **Step 3:**\\n  - For each `.cellsum` file, calculate the normalized reads and UMI per cell by dividing by the per-sample sum and multiplying by 1e6.\\n\\n- **Step 4:**\\n  - Use R to generate the required plots based on the processed data.\\n  - Ensure each plot is saved in the `output/` directory with the specified filenames.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, "logprob": null}, "reward": 0.0, "truncated": false, "done": false, "value": 0.0, "metadata": {}}
{"timestep": 4, "agent_state": {"tools": [{"type": "function", "info": {"name": "run_shell", "description": "Run a shell command in the task work_dir (bash -lc).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"command": {"description": "Shell command string passed to `bash -lc`.", "title": "Command", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["command"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "read_text_file", "description": "Read a UTF-8 text file relative to work_dir.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"relative_path": {"description": "Path under the workspace (not absolute).", "title": "Relative Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["relative_path"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "write_text_file", "description": "Write text to a path under work_dir (creates parent dirs).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"relative_path": {"description": "Path under the workspace (not absolute).", "title": "Relative Path", "type": "string"}, "content": {"description": "Full file body to write as UTF-8 text.", "title": "Content", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["relative_path", "content"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "run_rscript", "description": "Run inline R code via Rscript -e (single line safe for agents).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"code": {"description": "R expression passed as the argument to `Rscript -e`.", "title": "Code", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["code"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "list_workdir", "description": "List workspace as JSON (bounded depth).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {}, "required": []}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "write_plan", "description": "Persist a markdown plan to `workspace/.plan.md` (overwrite on rewrite).\n\nUse this at the start of a task and whenever the plan needs revision. The\nplan is not shown automatically on later steps; call check_progress to see\nthe current plan excerpt alongside deliverable state.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"plan": {"description": "Markdown text describing the step-by-step plan (bullet list).", "title": "Plan", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["plan"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "check_progress", "description": "Log a progress note and return a JSON snapshot of deliverables + plan excerpt.\n\nAppends `<UTC ISO timestamp> <note>` to `workspace/.progress.log`, then\nreturns a JSON string containing:\n  - `output_files`: list of {name, size_bytes} under `workspace/output/`.\n  - `success_artifact_present`: whether the task's success artifact glob matches.\n  - `plan_excerpt`: first 1000 chars of `.plan.md` (or empty if missing).\n  - `note_count`: total notes logged so far.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"note": {"description": "Short progress note to append to the log (plain text, one line).", "title": "Note", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["note"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "submit_done", "description": "End the episode. Set success=true only if criteria met (agent-declared).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"success": {"description": "Whether the agent believes the task objective is satisfied.", "title": "Success", "type": "boolean"}, "summary": {"default": "", "description": "Short optional note for logging.", "title": "Summary", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["success"]}}}], "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "# Task `snakepipes_scrna_qc`\n\n# Real R-task: snakepipes_scrna_qc\n\n**Pipeline provenance:** `maxplanck-ie-snakepipes-finish` (family: `scrna`).\nThis workspace is derived from a real R script in the source workflow. The ground-truth\nreference output used for offline scoring lives outside this workspace and is not\naccessible to you during execution.\n\n## Your goal\n\nYou are given a directory `input/qc/` containing per-library QC summaries for four\nlibraries across two plates:\n  - `<sample>.cellsum`: tab-delimited `sample, cell_idx, READS_UNIQFEAT, UMI`\n  - `<sample>.libsum`: headerless four-column table (`sample, metric, value, pct`)\n\nUsing an output prefix `output/scrna_qc`, compute:\n  - `scrna_qc.libstats_reads.tsv`: per-library metrics (reads) as a wide table\n  - `scrna_qc.libstats_pct.tsv`: per-library metrics (percentages) as a wide table\nAnd render these per-plate PNGs (2 libraries per plate):\n  - `scrna_qc.reads_UMI_plot.png`\n  - `scrna_qc.plate_cUPM.png`\n  - `scrna_qc.plate_cRPM.png`\n  - `scrna_qc.plate_abs_transcripts.png`\nNormalize reads/UMI per cell by per-sample sum * 1e6 before the z-score heatmap.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/scrna_qc.reads_UMI_plot.png` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: scrna_qc.libstats_reads.tsv, scrna_qc.libstats_pct.tsv, scrna_qc.reads_UMI_plot.png, scrna_qc.plate_cUPM.png, scrna_qc.plate_cRPM.png, scrna_qc.plate_abs_transcripts.png under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"qc\": {\n      \"cell_names.tsv\": {\n        \"_file\": \"cell_names.tsv\"\n      },\n      \"plate1_lib1.cellsum\": {\n        \"_file\": \"plate1_lib1.cellsum\"\n      },\n      \"plate1_lib1.libsum\": {\n        \"_file\": \"plate1_lib1.libsum\"\n      },\n      \"plate1_lib2.cellsum\": {\n        \"_file\": \"plate1_lib2.cellsum\"\n      },\n      \"plate1_lib2.libsum\": {\n        \"_file\": \"plate1_lib2.libsum\"\n      },\n      \"plate2_lib1.cellsum\": {\n        \"_file\": \"plate2_lib1.cellsum\"\n      },\n      \"plate2_lib1.libsum\": {\n        \"_file\": \"plate2_lib1.libsum\"\n      },\n      \"plate2_lib2.cellsum\": {\n        \"_file\": \"plate2_lib2.cellsum\"\n      },\n      \"plate2_lib2.libsum\": {\n        \"_file\": \"plate2_lib2.libsum\"\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/scrna_qc.reads_UMI_plot.png` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_BwHsVkLNgmj3iVo6FM0lBbfg", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Read the contents of the `input/qc/` directory to understand the structure and data within the `.cellsum` and `.libsum` files.\\n2. Process the `.libsum` files to create two wide tables: `scrna_qc.libstats_reads.tsv` and `scrna_qc.libstats_pct.tsv`.\\n3. Process the `.cellsum` files to normalize reads/UMI per cell by per-sample sum * 1e6.\\n4. Generate the required PNG plots:\\n   - `scrna_qc.reads_UMI_plot.png`\\n   - `scrna_qc.plate_cUPM.png`\\n   - `scrna_qc.plate_cRPM.png`\\n   - `scrna_qc.plate_abs_transcripts.png`\\n5. Save all outputs in the `output/` directory.\\n6. Verify the presence of `output/scrna_qc.reads_UMI_plot.png` and submit the task as complete.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (658 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_BwHsVkLNgmj3iVo6FM0lBbfg"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_ILi5phhVlP7ICINxeDHW04GM", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{}", "name": "list_workdir"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"qc\": {\n      \"cell_names.tsv\": {\n        \"_file\": \"cell_names.tsv\"\n      },\n      \"plate1_lib1.cellsum\": {\n        \"_file\": \"plate1_lib1.cellsum\"\n      },\n      \"plate1_lib1.libsum\": {\n        \"_file\": \"plate1_lib1.libsum\"\n      },\n      \"plate1_lib2.cellsum\": {\n        \"_file\": \"plate1_lib2.cellsum\"\n      },\n      \"plate1_lib2.libsum\": {\n        \"_file\": \"plate1_lib2.libsum\"\n      },\n      \"plate2_lib1.cellsum\": {\n        \"_file\": \"plate